title: Watch: Andrew Nemec discusses Oregon State Beavers rise, Oregon Ducks big weekend
text:
The Oregon Ducks and Oregon State Beavers have both had a big week on the recruiting trail.
Oregon is hosting several big-time prospects, including five-star linebacker Caleb Kelly and the top uncommitted quarterback in the class of 2017, Ryan Kelley .
On the other hand, Oregon State travels to Arizona this weekend, which means the it doesn't have a chance to host official visitors.
Instead, the Beavers ended a two-year streak without a four-star recruit, landing pledges from both Christian Wallace and Shurod Thompson .
